Madame Li's thoughts drifted back to the early days, when she and Old Li had first started the business. They had worked tirelessly, side by side, to build a reputation for producing the finest silk in the region. Their fabrics had been sought after by the wealthy and the noble, and their shop had been a hub of activity, filled with the hum of looms and the chatter of workers.

